 w year and the 11th month of the biblical Hebrew year. It has 30 days and 
 corresponds to January or February on the Gregorian calendar. רֹאשׁ 
 חוֹדֶשׁ\, transliterated Rosh Chodesh or Rosh Hodesh\, is a minor h
 oliday that occurs at the beginning of every month in the Hebrew calendar.
