 29 days and corresponds to April or May on the Gregorian calendar. רֹא
 שׁ חוֹדֶשׁ\, transliterated Rosh Chodesh or Rosh Hodesh\, is a mi
 nor holiday that occurs at the beginning of every month in the Hebrew cale
 ndar. It is marked by the birth of a new moon\n\nTorah: Numbers 28:1-15\n\
 nhttps://hebcal.com/h/rosh-chodesh-iyyar-2026?us=api&um=icalendar
