  days and corresponds to October or November on the Gregorian calendar. 
 רֹאשׁ חוֹדֶשׁ\, transliterated Rosh Chodesh or Rosh Hodesh\, i
 s a minor holiday that occurs at the beginning of every month in the Hebre
 w calendar. It is marked by the birth of a new moon\n\nTorah: Numbers 28:1
 -15\n\nhttps://hebcal.com/h/rosh-chodesh-cheshvan-2026?us=api&um=icalendar
